ZH: 冰山在冬天时非常美丽。
EN: The iceberg is very beautiful in winter.

ZH: 我们从远处就能看到那座巨大的冰山。
EN: We could see the huge iceberg from far away.

ZH: 冰山上覆盖着厚厚的积雪。
EN: The iceberg is covered with thick snow.

ZH: 小船正驶向那座巨大的冰山。
EN: The small boat is sailing towards the giant iceberg.

ZH: 冰山上有一只可爱的北极熊。
EN: There is a cute polar bear on the iceberg.

ZH: 冰山在海面上漂浮着。
EN: The iceberg is floating on the sea.

ZH: 冰山的颜色是纯净的白色。
EN: The iceberg is pure white in color.

ZH: 这座冰山的形状非常奇特。
EN: The shape of this iceberg is very unique.

ZH: 冰山是由冰川压缩形成的。
EN: Icebergs are formed by the compression of glaciers.

ZH: 冰山的质地非常坚硬。
EN: The iceberg has a very hard texture.

ZH: 冰山是地球上最壮观的自然景观之一。
EN: Icebergs are one of the most spectacular natural landscapes on Earth.

ZH: 冰山可以飘浮在海面上数年之久。
EN: Icebergs can float on the sea for several years.

ZH: 冰山在冬天时可能会变得更加壮丽。
EN: Icebergs may become even more magnificent in winter.

ZH: 冰山通常是海水结冰形成的。
EN: Icebergs are usually formed by freezing seawater.

ZH: 冰山上蕴含着丰富的水资源。
EN: Icebergs contain rich water resources.

ZH: 冰山是极地地区的一种特有景观。
EN: Icebergs are a unique landscape in polar regions.

ZH: 冰山的高度往往远远高于海平面。
EN: The height of icebergs is often much higher than sea level.

ZH: 冰山在融化时会释放大量的淡水。
EN: Icebergs release a lot of fresh water when they melt.

ZH: 冰山是海洋生态系统中的重要组成部分。
EN: Icebergs are an important component of marine ecosystems.
